.TH CLN 1 "January 2026" "cln 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cln \- recursively clean temporary and junk files from directories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cln
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPATH\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cln
searches for and removes common editor backup files, crash files, and other
temporary files that accumulate in working directories.
.PP
By default, cln prompts before deleting files. Use \fB\-P\fR for non-interactive
operation.
.SH DEFAULT PATTERNS
The following file patterns are removed by default:
.TP
.B *~
Editor backup files (Emacs, nano, etc.)
.TP
.B ~*
Alternate backup format
.TP
.B .~*
Hidden backup files
.TP
.B .*~
Hidden files ending with tilde
.TP
.B DEADJOE
Joe editor crash files
.TP
.B dead.letter
Unsent mail files
.TP
.B wget-log*
wget download logs
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-n ", " \-\-prompt
Prompt before deleting files. This is the default behavior.
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-N ", " \-\-no\-prompt
Delete files without prompting.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase output verbosity. Use twice for debug output (shows find expressions).
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output.
.TP
.BI \-m " N" "\fR, \fP" \-\-depth " N"
Set maximum directory depth to recurse. Default is 3.
Use \-1 for unlimited depth.
.TP
.BI \-a " SPEC" "\fR, \fP" \-\-add " SPEC"
Add file pattern(s) to the cleanup scan. Can be specified multiple times.
SPEC can be comma-delimited for multiple patterns.
.TP
.BI \-S " SPEC" "\fR, \fP" \-\-set " SPEC"
Set/replace all file patterns, overriding config files and defaults.
SPEC can be comma-delimited for multiple patterns.
.TP
.B \-L
Follow symbolic links during search. By default, symbolic links are not followed.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 22
Invalid argument or missing required option value.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Clean current directory with prompting:
.B cln
.TP
Clean /tmp without prompting:
.B cln \-P /tmp
.TP
Quiet mode, no prompts:
.B cln \-Pq /var/cache
.TP
Add custom patterns:
.B cln \-a \(aq*.bak,*.tmp\(aq .
.TP
Deep clean with depth 7:
.B cln \-Pqm 7 /home/user
.TP
Clean multiple directories:
.B cln \-P dir1 dir2 dir3
.TP
Replace default patterns entirely:
.B cln \-S \(aq*.tmp,*.old\(aq /tmp
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/etc/default/cln
User configuration file. One pattern per line. Comments start with #.
.TP
.I /etc/default/cln
System-wide configuration file. Used if user config does not exist.
.TP
.I ~/.bashrc
Can be used to create aliases for common cln invocations.
.SH NOTES
When prompted, respond with:
.TP
.B y
Yes, delete the listed files
.TP
Any other key
Skip this directory
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR find (1),
.BR rm (1)
